      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis damage model must be justified for the flow regime and validated against relevant benchmark data.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on documented performance for rotating machinery flows with adverse pressure gradients. Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model applied with literature-validated coefficients. Model form choices documented with supporting references. Sensitivity of RHI predictions to turbulence model variant (k-epsilon vs. SST k-omega) evaluated; SST k-omega showed superior agreement with experimental data."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material properties and boundary conditions must be characterized with documented sources and uncertainty estimates.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity characterized via rheometry at 37°C; density from literature. Inlet velocity profiles derived from upstream flow conditioning measurements. Outlet pressure boundary conditions set to match experimental pump curve. All input parameter sources documented. Sensitivity analysis performed for viscosity and inlet turbulence intensity; RHI predictions insensitive to ±10% variation in these parameters."
    },
